title: For Sale:  6.5x55 Swede Mauser wooden blanks
postcontent:
What I have for sale here is 6.5x55 Swedish Mauser Wooden Blank Ammunition.

1 box = 100 rounds.



This ammo does not appear to have any corrosion on the exterior of the cartridges.


This looks to be clean, new brass with a crimp for the bullet.


I have translated (via Google) the writing on the label.

The translation is below.
-----------------------------------------

Defence Ordnance Management
100 pc.
6.5 mm loose cartridges m/46
Ammunition lot: 54-03
Powder Lot: B (1.3 x0, 15) 53 H01
Chuck Ring Date: December 18, 1954

Manufactured by A/S Danish Munitions Factory

-------------------------------------------



Some information about these cartridges:

http://translate.google.com/translate?js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vaabenhistoriskselskab.dk%2Farma-dania%2F_AD_patroner_view.php%3Feditid1%3D53&act=url



This link contains a photo of a cartridge with a knurled ring near the base.

I believe this knurled ring signifies a reloaded cartridge, due to other cartridges on that site remarking on this knurled ring.


This ammunition I am selling does not have this knurled ring, which would lead me to believe that this brass is new/unfired.


I am assuming this brass is Berdan primed due to the country of origin and time frame of manufacture ... but the truth is I haven't disassembled any of the ammunition to find out.


Headstamps are mixed.


Pics are representative headstamps that I found after about 30 seconds of digging through the box.

Cool ammo for the Swede Mauser collector or shooter

Price : asking $20/box of 100

This price does not include S/H.

The MAS-36 is a short, carbine-style rifle with a two-piece stock and slab-sided receiver.
